  "prompt": "Is Economics good major?",
  "response": "Whether Economics is a good major depends on your personal interests, career goals, and strengths. Here are some pros and cons:\n\nPros:\n1. Wide range of career opportunities\n2. Good earning potential\n3. Develops strong analytical and critical thinking skills\n4. Applicable to many industries\n5. Good preparation for graduate studies\n6. Can lead to careers in finance, consulting, government, academia\n\nCons:\n1. Can be mathematically challenging\n2. Requires strong quantitative skills\n3. Some jobs may require advanced degrees\n4. Can be abstract and theoretical\n5. Competitive job market\n\nIdeal for people who:\n- Enjoy math and statistical analysis\n- Like problem-solving\n- Are interested in understanding market dynamics\n- Want versatile career options\n\nPotential career paths:\n- Economist\n- Financial analyst\n- Management consultant\n- Investment banker\n- Policy advisor\n- Data analyst\n- Market researcher\n\nUltimately, the value of an Economics major depends on your individual goals, skills, and passion for the subject.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further?",
